      <byline class="print_byline">By DAVID STOUT</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Presidents come and go, but Helen Thomas stayed at the White House for 39 years. Ms. Thomas, who is 79 and covered John F. Kennedy and every president thereafter for United Press International, quit after the financially troubled news service was acquired by a group with links to the Unification Church.</p>
        <p>DAVID STOUT</p>
      </block>
